Commentary Text: Bumrah to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! Taken! Bumrah ends the innings with a couple of wickets. A fast full toss on the stumps, Rinku Singh gave it his all to clear the field near long-on, but could not get the distance. Hardik is well inside the rope as he takes it calmly. Rinku Singh c Hardik Pandya b Bumrah 4(6)

Commentary Text: Bumrah to Uthappa, out Caught by Rohit!! The pain, the suffering comes to an end. The off-cutter from Bumrah and it dips on Uthappa, who looks to go across the line, the toe-end goes straight up and Rohit settles under it near extra cover. He walks back to the dressing room and would love to be a fly in there. Uthappa c Rohit b Bumrah 40(47) [4s-1 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Malinga to A Russell, out Caught by de Kock!! Oh dear! The faces in the KKR dugout tell it all. Russell picked the wrong day to fail. His first single digit score and it has come in a crunch game. He doesn't walk back to the dugout but climbs up the stairs and goes into the dressing room. Malinga's ploy to bowl round the wicket has worked. Dug in short and gets it to climb near chest high, Russell arches back to evade it but leaves his gloves hanging mid-air, there is a brush and de Kock does the rest. Umpire Nandan took his time but eventually made the right decision. Russell didn't bother to have a word with Uthappa for the review as he knew he had got something on it. A Russell c de Kock b Malinga 0(1)

Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Chris Lynn, out Caught by de Kock!! Hardik Pandya is turning it on for MI. "You cannot keep Hardik out of the game," chirps Kevin Pietersen on air. It was the slower ball, lands it well outside off making Lynn to fetch for it. The batsman accepts the challenge and reaches out aiming for a biggie. Terribly mistimes, slicing it up off a top-edge. QdK back-tracks, calls for it and nestles in his gloves. Huge blow for KKR this. Chris Lynn c de Kock b Hardik Pandya 41(29) [4s-2 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, out Lbw!! Gill walks off after having a chat with his partner. The golden arm of Hardik strikes for MI and KKR lose their first wicket. Gill wasn't looking fluid from the start, found it difficult to get going and Hardik has trapped him. It was the off-paced delivery, dipped upon pitching and the batsman was caught playing down the wrong line. Completely missed it, getting struck in-line with the stumps. HawkEye confirms that it's crashing into middle and leg stump. The blue flags are out and MI fans are elated. Shubman Gill lbw b Hardik Pandya 9(16)

Commentary Text: Prasidh to de Kock, out Caught by Karthik! What a deperately fantastic catch that is! A short one at the body, de Kock isn't second-time lucky with a top-edged hook, skies it towards fine leg, looks, for an eternity, like it will land in no man's land, but Karthik, the stubborn Karthik, chases it down from the 'keeper's stop and dives full-stretch to take a magnificent catch. It's that kind of inspirational moment by the skipper, the kind of fairytale moment, that can turn a match, or even a tournament, on its head. de Kock c Karthik b Prasidh 30(23) [4s-1 6s-3]
